@node  "Rename"  "MegaD 3.1 ARexx Commands Copyright © 1993 John L. Jones"

    Command:   Rename

      Usage:   Rename [filename]

Description:   If no argument is sent, this will operate the same as
               the "Rename" built-in command.
               
               If an argument is sent, the argument must be the
               filename you wish to rename the first selected item to.
               Once it is renamed, the item will be unselected.
               
               If Keep .info is selected, the .info file will be
               renamed also.

               --------------------------------------------------------------

    Example:   DO FOREVER
               
                  NextItem Filename
                  if result = "" then leave
                  
                  ELSE DO
                     /* add underscore for new name */
                     name = '_' || result
                     
                     /* Rename will unselect the first
                        selected item */
                     Rename name
                  END
               
               /* skip the next selected item */
               END

               --------------------------------------------------------------

   Built-In:   @{" Rename " link "MegaD.Guide/Command Rename"}

   See Also:   RenameOther.rexx script


@endnode





